			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				arg... you realize that by creating new items as no drop there is no way that many of us will ever be able to get them. i personaly dont get to play as much as others so i find that to aquire the equipment that i desire i HAVE to buy or trade for it. THIS is how an economy works. i dont have the time, desire, will power or whatever it takes to camp a six hour spawn. if this item suddenly becomes no drop... guess what! my chances of getting this object just shoot from &quot;maybe if i can come up with enough money or some good trade.&quot; to &quot;NILL!&quot;. <BR>
granted the twink problem is just that. a problem. but do you realize just how much work it is to get a full suit of ro armor? its not like the &quot;bord level 50 wiz&quot; just pulled the full suit off of a Sand Giant corpse. this is a long and very difficult quest. personaly i feel that if the level 50 wiz wants to complete the quest and give a full suit to a level 1 pally then he has every right to do so because it will probably take him a good amount of time. this also isnt going to show up as much as you seem to think. i do see full bronze and crafted twinks and it makes me laugh a little because all the chalenge is lost for those people and i cant imagine how much fun a game with no chalenge could be. now granted you state the problem with trade skills such as smithing and the creation of &quot;twinks&quot; and how the &quot;twinks&quot; are destroying the economy. now i have to disagree just slightly to this. i will grant you that the twink isnt going to need any banded any time soon, but there are lots of new players buying everquest every day. a good friend of mine is a master smith and she sells enough of her trade to keep herself very happy and quite rich. <BR>
just take these coments as my personal observations, they only apply to what i have seen and i could be oblivious to the truth. but when i get on eq i dont powerlevel and go for the next level or the next best piece of equipment, i play the game as i feel it was ment to be played... for fun. everybody should just relax a bit, take a deep breath, and go hang out in a newbie zone for a while. its gobs of fun and you get to meet people that are experianceing eq for the first time. just talking to them is more gratifying to me than camping a rare mob or makeing that next level.<BR>
<BR>
Heckunderhill Took<BR>
30th druid EM<BR>
