	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay I have wanted a public place to comment on this for quite a while.... and here we go...<BR>
<BR>
Some of you are claiming that making items NO DROP will ruin the economy.  Yeah, it might have a bad effect on some aspects of it, but it will definietly improve conditions with one of the current problems with the economy.....<BR>
<BR>
That, my friends, is twinking.<BR>
<BR>
Not catching on?  Okay, here goes.<BR>
<BR>
Situation:  A level 50 Wizard is bored, so he starts a new Pally with Full Ro, Ghoulbane, and a Mithril 2H.  With me so far?  He then moves on through the levels.  He arrives at level 10.  Around this time, most tanks are working on banded/ringmail armor, if not bronze.  This lowbie though, does not require either, as he is wearing full plate.  A Smith in the area is trying to up his skill, he's at about 95-110.  He is working on armor now, but there's a problem.... there's nobody to sell it to.  Nope, noone.  Maybe the occaisonal newbie.  Why?  Everyone is already sporting gear twice as good as even his own.  It gets sold to a merchant, never enters circulation.  The smith is now losing money on the skill... as it is not cheap to do.  <BR>
<BR>
Another problem we are facing that stems from this, is that lower-level drops are no longer worth anything.  That Dwarven Ringmail Tunic that you fought long and hard for back at level 18 and sold for a hefty 35pp is now usually given out free.  The SBH has lost its value, once 125pp, now you're lucky to get 50.  Why?  Well if YOU had had an Executioner's Axe at level 15 would YOU have bought an SBH?  I think not....<BR>
<BR>
Farming, Twinking, *those* are some of the problems with EQ's economy.  While it's not a cure, making more items NO DROP will help these other problems.  Put things in perspective folks...<BR>
<BR>
Ahh well, there's my 2cp.  Feel free to comment on this, as I am open to discussion.<BR>
<BR>
Fanon Faythunder<BR>
Level 27 Paladin of the Legion of Fate<BR>
Erollisi Marr
